      | c = as $p^2 = \paren {-p}^2$ and $q^2 = \paren {-q}^2$
}}
{{end-eqn}}
and so $\tuple {-p, -q}$ is also a point on $\KK$.
Hence the result by definition of center of symmetry.
{{qed}}
